cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper discusses the use of self-organizing maps (SOMs) for storing and transferring knowledge in reinforcement learning. SOMs are a popular technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence, which makes cs.LG and cs.AI the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of SOMs in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY), which further supports these categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks (cs.NE) in conjunction with SOMs, which is another strong indicator of these categories.
